<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-13276] Regression on CASSANDRA-11416: can&apos;t load snapshots of tables with dropped columns</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-13276</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m running Cassandra 3.10 and running into the exact same issue described in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-11416&quot; title=&quot;No longer able to load backups into new cluster if there was a dropped column&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-11416&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-11416&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. A table is created with columns &apos;a&apos; and &apos;b&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
2. Data is written to the table&lt;br/&gt;
3. Drop column &apos;b&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
4. Take a snapshot&lt;br/&gt;
5. Drop the table&lt;br/&gt;
6. Run the snapshot schema.cql to recreate the table and the run the alter&lt;br/&gt;
7. Try to restore the snapshot data using sstableloader&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;sstableloader yields the error:&lt;br/&gt;
java.lang.RuntimeException: Unknown column b during deserialization&lt;/p&gt;</description>
